===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `find` baraye peyda kardan file-ha va pooshe-ha dar yek directory ya zir-directory-ha estefade mishavad. Shoma mitoonid bar asase name, size, tarikhe tagheer va khosusiate digar file-ha ra search konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `find . -name "esm-file.txt"`  --> 🔍 Peyda kardan file ba esm دقیق
    🔹 `find . -name "*esm-file*"`  --> 🎯 Peyda kardan file-haye ke esm-file dar esm-eshon bashe
    🔹 `find . -type f`  --> 📄 Peyda kardan faghat file-ha
    🔹 `find . -type d`  --> 📁 Peyda kardan faghat pooshe-ha
    🔹 `find . -size +10M` --> 📦 Peyda kardan file-haye bozorgtar az 10MB
    🔹 `find . -mtime -7` --> 📅 Peyda kardan file-haye ke dar 7 rooz gozashte tagheer karde and

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ find . -name "report.pdf"

    🔹 Peyda kardan file ba name `report.pdf` dar directory فعلی va zir-directory-ها

    $ find /home/user -size +50M -type f

    🔹 Peyda kardan file-haye bozorgtar az 50MB dar directory `/home/user` va zir-directory-ها

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ find . -name "*.jpg" -print

    🔹 Peyda kardan hameye file-haye JPG dar directory فعلی va chap kardan path اونها.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `find` command is used to locate files and directories within a directory hierarchy. You can search based on filename, size, modification time, and other file attributes.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `find . -name "filename.txt"`  --> 🔍 Find file with exact name
    🔹 `find . -name "*filename*"`  --> 🎯 Find files containing "filename" in their name
    🔹 `find . -type f`  --> 📄 Find only files
    🔹 `find . -type d`  --> 📁 Find only directories
    🔹 `find . -size +10M` --> 📦 Find files larger than 10MB
    🔹 `find . -mtime -7` --> 📅 Find files modified within the last 7 days

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ find . -name "report.pdf"

    🔹 Find a file named `report.pdf` in the current directory and its subdirectories.

    $ find /home/user -size +50M -type f

    🔹 Find files larger than 50MB in the `/home/user` directory and its subdirectories.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ find . -name "*.jpg" -print

    🔹 Find all JPG files in the current directory and print their paths.